.TH "ice_sched_set_node_bw_lmt" 9 "ice_sched_set_node_bw_lmt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ice_sched_set_node_bw_lmt \- set node's BW limit
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "enum ice_status" ice_sched_set_node_bw_lmt
.BI "(struct ice_port_info *pi "  ","
.BI "struct ice_sched_node *node "  ","
.BI "enum ice_rl_type rl_type "  ","
.BI "u32 bw "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pi" 12
port information structure
.IP "node" 12
tree node
.IP "rl_type" 12
rate limit type min, max, or shared
.IP "bw" 12
bandwidth in Kbps - Kilo bits per sec
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
It updates node's BW limit parameters like BW RL profile ID of type CIR,
EIR, or SRL. The caller needs to hold scheduler lock.
